'''Nathan Elias Hamill''' (born [[June 25]], [[1979]]) is an artist who had a cameo in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] and [[Saile Minnau]] in [[Star Wars: Episode VIII The Last Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VIII ''The Last Jedi'']]. He is the son of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] actor [[Mark Hamill]].

==Biography==
During the filming of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']], Mark Hamill was accompanied in [[Wikipedia:Finse|Finse]], [[Wikipedia:Norway|Norway]], by his wife Marilou, who was several months pregnant. In anticipation of a premature birth, the Hamills had brought medical supplies and a giant teddy bear with them. Nathan was born early on the Monday morning on which his father was meant to play a scene in which Luke manages to grab onto an electronic weather vane after emerging from the underside [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]]. Despite having stayed up all night, Mark Hamill arrived on time at the set to film his fall from Cloud City onto the exterior of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']].<ref name="BTM">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref>

Nathan Hamill made one cameo appearance in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']]. In an interview with the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine, he referred this character as "[[Rehtul Minnau]]," a name which was later canonized in [[Teckla Minnau/Legends|Teckla Minnau's]] entry in the [[StarWars.com]] [[Databank (original)|Databank]], albeit not confirmed to be the same character.

Hamill illustrated sketch cards for the ''[[2009 Topps Star Wars Galaxy Series 4]]'' trading card set.<ref name="2009 Topps SWGS4">{{Topps|set=2009 Topps Star Wars Galaxy Series 4|subset=Artist Sketch Cards|parent=1}}</ref>

